ANALYSIS.TITLE: TCGA/ICGC PanCancer Specimen-Level Alignment for Specimen CGP_specimen_1491214 from Participant CGP_donor_1437417
ANALYSIS.DESCRIPTION: Specimen-level BAM from the reference alignment of specimen CGP_specimen_1491214 from donor CGP_donor_1437417. This uses the SeqWare BWA-MEM PanCancer Workflow version 2.6.1 available at https://s3.amazonaws.com/oicr.workflow.bundles/released-bundles/Workflow_Bundle_BWA_2.6.1_SeqWare_1.0.15.zip. This workflow can be created from source, see https://github.com/SeqWare/public-workflows/tree/2.6.1/workflow-bwa-pancancer. For a complete change log see https://github.com/SeqWare/public-workflows/blob/2.6.1/workflow-bwa-pancancer/CHANGELOG.md. Input BAMs are prepared and submitted to GNOS server according to the submission SOP documented at: https://wiki.oicr.on.ca/display/PANCANCER/PCAP+%28a.k.a.+PAWG%29+Sequence+Submission+SOP+-+v1.0. Please note the reference is hs37d, see ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/technical/reference/phase2_reference_assembly_sequence/README_human_reference_20110707 for more information. Briefly this is the integrated reference sequence from the GRCh37 primary assembly (chromosomal plus unlocalized and unplaced contigs), the rCRS mitochondrial sequence (AC:NC_012920), Human herpesvirus 4 type 1 (AC:NC_007605) and the concatenated decoy sequences (hs37d5cs.fa.gz).

CUSTOM.DESCRIPTION: GRCh37 (hs37d5). See ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/technical/reference/phase2_reference_assembly_sequence/README_human_reference_20110707 for more information.
